1 Run Tasksel Using sudo tasksel
2 You Can Choose Whatever You Want (LXDE Is Recommended For Older Machines)
3 If You Are Installing LXDE I Would Recommend To Switch To LXDM (If LightDM Is Installed But Not LXDM) 
  1 Run sudo apt remove --purge lightdm
  2 Then Run sudo apt autoremove
  3 Install LXDM sudo apt install lxdm
  4 Reboot using sudo reboot
  
After You Install A Graphical Environment
Go To https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Adrenaline-Linux
The Download Adrenaline Linux Logo On Readme by Clicking Save Image As
If You See 544244630-03f6bf27-78f9-4378-a30d-8987fc5bd6ee.png Change It To adrenalinelinux-logo.png Then Save It To Download
Then sudo mv /home/yourname/Downloads/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/debian-logo.png
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/debian-security.png
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/desktop-base/debian-logos/logo.svg
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/desktop-base/debian-logos/logo-64.png
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/desktop-base/debian-logos/logo-128.png
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/desktop-base/debian-logos/logo-256.png
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/desktop-base/debian-logos/logo-text.svg
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/desktop-base/debian-logos/logo-text-64.png
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/desktop-base/debian-logos/logo-text-128.png
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/desktop-base/debian-logos/logo-text-256.png
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/desktop-base/debian-logos/logo-text-version.svg
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/desktop-base/debian-logos/logo-text-version-64.png
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/desktop-base/debian-logos/logo-text-version-128.png
Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/adrenalinelinux-logo.png /usr/share/desktop-base/debian-logos/logo-text-version-256.png

For KDE Plasma
Go To Notifications Then System Notifications Then Play a sound on login and logout sound then click apply
Then Go To Colors & Themes Then Change Debian Breeze To Breeze
Also Go To Login Screen SDDM Then Change Debian Breeze To Breeze then click apply

For GNOME
Click Right Mouse Then Change Background Then Change Debian Wallpaper To Adwaita Wallpaper
